        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-05T12:35:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This addresses the pixel diffs that came up in an earlier patch set. Basically, on platforms where we couldn\u0027t disable MSAA, the GrStencilMaskHelper would add ops marked as non-aa even though they\u0027d end up being MSAA\u0027ed anyways. This would confuse the pixel bounds calculations and change how the scissor was applied. Regardless of the rest of the CL, this helps keep the op state consistent with what will actually happen on the hardware.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 325,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 333,
        "endChar": 5
      },
